      "createdAt": "2026-03-22T20:35:03.811684+00:00",
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, thank you for telling me this. Seriously — that took courage, and I want you to know there's nothing to apologize for here. The instinct to push through and not want to admit something's gotten harder is incredibly human, and the fact that you're being honest now is what matters most.\n\nI have to be straight with you, though, because I care about getting this right: diagnosing what's happening with your foot and telling you how to treat it is genuinely outside what I'm qualified to do. I'm your running coach, not a medical professional — and plantar fasciitis that's worsening despite rest and easy running deserves a proper clinical eye. Guessing at a diagnosis from my end could actually steer you in the wrong direction, and that's the last thing either of us wants.\n\n**What I'd encourage you to do right now:**\nGet back in touch with your physiotherapist — the same one who cleared you — and let them know what's happened over the last three weeks: the pain that's been building, the runs you've had to cut short, and that you've been running through it. They need the full picture to assess where things stand.\n\n**What I can do:**\n\nOnce you've spoken with them and have updated guidance, I'm ready to rebuild your plan around whatever they recommend — whether that's a full pause, modified activity, or something else entirely. We've already shown, in those first few weeks of training history, that you can come back from this carefully and smartly. That foundation doesn't disappear.\n\nIn the meantime — and only if your physio hasn't already advised you to stop completely — it would be worth pausing the running until you've had that conversation. Not as a setback, but as the move that protects everything you're working toward.\n\nOne question before you go: do you have easy access to your physiotherapist, or is there anything getting in the way of reaching out to them?"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_012uAZSBYyYbrfYzRfiS16hF"
    }
